# Open Notebook → Flock (OpenAI-compatible)
# NotebookLM-style sources → chat + podcast, but pointed at YOUR models.

# Option A — Docker Compose (recommended). Add these to .env in the
# open-notebook clone next to docker-compose.yml:

OPENAI_API_BASE_URL={{.BaseURL}}/v1
OPENAI_API_KEY={{.Token}}
# Optional — pin a default model. Pick a context-window-friendly one
# (Qwen, Llama 4 Scout, or Gemma 4 work well for long sources):
OPEN_NOTEBOOK_DEFAULT_MODEL={{.Model}}

# Then in the open-notebook directory:
#   docker compose up -d
#
# Open http://localhost:8501 (or whatever port the compose file maps).

# Option B — Configure in the UI (no env vars):
#   Settings → API Keys → Add Credential
#     Provider:  OpenAI Compatible
#     Base URL:  {{.BaseURL}}/v1
#     API Key:   {{.Token}}
#   Save. Models list auto-populates from /v1/models.

# For embedding-driven source indexing, install an embedding model
# in Flock first:
#   flock model add nomic-embed-text
# then pick `nomic-embed-text` in Open Notebook's embedding provider.
